  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6775.68 sitting below the 6793 flip line and in PIN regime, dealers are currently buying the dip as they're long gamma and providing stabilizing flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (+57B) will create significant selling pressure on any rally attempt, while the negative gamma pocket at 6770 (-30B) should provide buying support if we drift lower. The recent GEX surge combined with the tight 6770-6800 range suggests dealers will aggressively defend both levels, creating a strong two-way market with limited breakout potential.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6770-6800 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
